<plot>With the world on the verge of a third World War, God witnessing the failure of his creation and the loss of ever achieving a utopia, decides to take a final stand. He chooses two people from Earth. One is an Arab young man whose past is that of tragedy and horror. The other is an American woman whose tough experiences have strengthened her personally and spiritually. God then places the two in a secluded white room where they are told to come up with a unanimous decision before the World War begins. The choices for the decision are thus: Press the red button which will ultimately reset the world from the very beginning, giving mankind another chance to start from point zero; or wait and hope that mankind will decide not to go through another world war. With time running out, the two must reach a compromise or the fate of the world will be forever doomed.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?412263</url></doc>
